Alembic migrations for SteamAgent.

The database URL and target schema come from the app itself (env.py reads
`settings.database_url` and `Base.metadata`), so you don't edit a URL here.

Common commands (from the repo root):

    uv run alembic current                              # show the DB's current revision
    uv run alembic history                              # list revisions
    uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "msg"     # draft a migration from model changes
    uv run alembic upgrade head                         # apply pending migrations
    uv run alembic downgrade -1                          # roll back one revision

The app also runs `upgrade head` automatically on startup
(see src/steam_agent/storage/migrate.py). Existing databases created by the old
`create_all()` are stamped at the baseline, not recreated, so no data is lost.
Always review an autogenerated revision before committing it.
